	   <a name=98355031620233></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98355031620233><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=98355031620233>RE: What about Bash? Why 1-hb or 2-hs?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=98355031620233#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=17094><span id=Sage>Kneesmasher</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>397 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Mar 2nd 11:25 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.75]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Valderessa, You ask why you would switch to blunt weapons or 2-hs. There really is no COMPELLING reason to improve your blunt skills, other than the fact that it will expand the weapon selections you have at higher levels. Right now at higher levels, Paladin weapon selection is somewhat limited. Hopefully Verant will continue to work on that.<br><br>You can continue with 1-hs/bash for the rest of your Paladin career without much trouble, but that will exclude you from using such swords as Soulfire, Fiery Avenger & the coveted Fiery Defender. They are all 2-hs weapons. Also, my dream weapon, the Jade Inlaid Crescent Axe is 2-hs, among others.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>There are some very nice 1-hb & 2-hb weapons out there at higher levels that you may be interested in and you won't get a chance if your 1-hb weapon skill awful.  But, you certainly don't have to do it. It's just something to improve your options later on.<br><br>I would, however, HIGHLY recommend that you continue to keep your 2-hs skill up and maxed.  Without a maxed 2-hs skill you are excluding yourself from some very nice Paladin only weapons. There will also be times when a 2-hs is preferable, such as when fighting mobs with big damage shields.  The faster your weapon, the more damage YOU are taking from their damage shield. Since you are still at 10th level, you probably haven't faced this yet, but you will.  So there are times you will need to pull out the big gun and hit slower but for more damage per hit. Otherwise, the damage shield will chew you up, which means more healing, which chews up mana in the group.<br><br>Keep 1-hs/bash and 2-hs maxed. The 1-hb & 2-hb is nothing but gravy!<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>34th Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
