	   <tr><td colspan=2>Yes, keep using your 1-hs and mashing the BASH button.&nbsp;&nbsp;It takes quite a while for your Bash to catch up to your 1-hs or 2-hs.  I started 1-hs at level 28 (WAY too late) and have been working on my Bash every since.  It isn't maxed yet, but it's getting better! I think it is at about 160 now, so I'm close to maxed on Bash.<br><br>Just keep after it. I wouldn't spent points on it because it will come up on its own.  Also, don't forget about 1-hb and 2-hb!! It's not too late!  <br><br>Everytime I level, I make sure I switch weapons back and forth until my 1-hs and 2-hs are maxed. If only I had done that at level 1!!<br><br>Good luck<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>34th Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
