	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Mar 1st 3:24 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.20]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>To tell you the truth, I've never seen a point to investing any of your skill points in a trade skill.&nbsp;&nbsp;You will only be able to invest 20 points into a trade skill.  After you have attained 20 points in a trade, you can't invest anymore into it.  The first 20 points in any trade are the easiest to gain through simple practice.  (and cheap, too)  On that note, I've never seen a point in investing skill points in weapon practice, either.  That, too, goes up quickly through practice.  (for free)  The only thing keeping skill points absolutely worthless is the languages.  They add an interesting chance to master some obscure language and teach it to others.  The only real skills you need to worry about training in are those combat skills that require you to put 1 point in to start using it, like bash, riposte, double attack, dodge, parry, etc.  After 1 point is invested, it will go up through use, over time.  Enough blathering out of me now.  It's your skill points, don't let me tell you what to do with em.  =)<br><br>Souldragoon Flamingheart<br>43rd circle Paladin of Virtue<br>Master of Elder Dragon speech  =P<br>Fennin Ro<br>&nbsp;<br><i>Follow virtue, and the virtuous will follow you.</i></td></tr>
