	   <a name=98338646177474></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98338646177474><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=98338646177474>RE: FP militia KOS</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=98338646177474#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2300><span id=Sage>DrophWayseeker</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>44 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Feb 28th 1:54 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.55]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>You will definitely be KOS by the time you obtain Soulfire unless you take steps to raise your FP Militia faction.&nbsp;&nbsp;The quest for Soulfire includes killing Sir Lucan, the head of the FP Militia.<br><br>There are several quests to raise faction with the FP militia, and a few do not give negative hits with any good groups. I recommend going that route, as maintaining faction with one group and trying to balance another can become quite complicated. The best quests I can suggest are the goblin ears and orc/gnoll scalp quests in Highkeep/Highpass. You get positive faction hits with FP militia and Corrupt Guards of Qeynos with NO negative hits to good groups.<br><br>As far as getting to N FP from EC, that's actually pretty simple. In W FP along the North wall in the newbie area, there is a secret tunnel that leads to N FP avoiding all the Militia. YOu should be careful, though, as there is sometimes a Dark Elf inside the entrance (he is dubious to me), and he may aggro on you (I'm not sure what factions he is).<br><br>Getting to the boat is a little more complicated, though. There is another sewer route from N FP to W FP that involves a short run possibly past a  Militia guard or two to E FP. From there, you will need invis to get past the guards and get to the boat.  Of course, you can avoid the sewer run if you just start out with invis. Same thing for leaving the boat, of course. Alternatively, just pay the 10-20pp for a port to whereever you need to go, as that's a lot less likely to get you killed if the invis fails (and it has a really nasty habit of doing it at the worst possible time).<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
