	   <tr><td colspan=2>Faction for Freeport Paladins (Hall of Truth), the easiest thing to do is kill orcs in the commons (pawns, centurions, legonaires, ect.). It is by far the easiest way to gain faction at your lvl. you can easily kill an orc pawn by shooting an arrow at it, I can anyway.<br><br>Faction for Qeynos Paladins (Temple of Life)- Run to Queynos and convert about 100pp to gold pieces...Run to the temple of life and look for Lashun Novashine who is sporadically on the ramp leading to the gyrating disk of the temple of life. If he is not there wait, he will eventually walk on or appear there.&nbsp;&nbsp;/con him. Hand him 2gp at a time until you are AMIABLE with the temple of life. (You may continue to hand him 2 gp at a time until you are warmly but that takes hours on end) Now, there is a paladin knight that swims in this nice pool underneath the ramp, he is guarding the fish inside the pool. And a great way to raise faction QUICKLY is to kill these fish "Koalandi" and the fish that sometimes loots from their corpses is handed to the paladin swimming in the pool, and as long as you are at least amiable with the priests of life it will give you a NICE faction boost with the temple. Now you must understand killing these fish  gives you negative faction, so the best way to get these fish to the paladin is to have a friend create a mule, or new character to use  (preferably a human warrior) and kill the fish - another note is that you must stay near the edges of the pool to avoid being killed by the  paladin in the water...Now, have your friend or hired newbie =) kill fish and let you loot them, immediately giving the looted fish to the paladin swimming.Depends, but it works well, and is faster than the 2gp method. As soon as you are warmly with temple of life, you are done with this part. Also, beware what you kill...lots of NPCs in norrath will give you negative faction hits with temple - so if you get a hit immediately go back to queynos and raise it back to warmly. (courtesy of everlore.com) -<a href="http://www.everlore.com/quests/default.asp?mode=35&id=276851&hl=276851" target=_new>http://www.everlore.com/quests/default.asp?mode=35&id=276851&hl=276851</a><br>&nbsp;<br>Dadin <br>54th Cavalier<br>Honored Circle on Xev<br><br>Dwarven Thane<br>Hellwinds - Palomides </td></tr>
