	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98333498661584><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=98333498661584>RE: What shield to use at Lvl 13?  SBS to start</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=98333498661584#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=17094><span id=Sage>Kneesmasher</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>397 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Feb 27th 11:36 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.47]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Tenniel, I applaud your effort in keeping your 1-hb up and not jumping to 1-hs and 2-hs like every other paladin I know...including me! You are way ahead of the game.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, you cannot forget about 1-hs and 2-hs. You do need to keep all of these skills up.  Even 2-hb is a great skill to have since at higher levels there are some awesome 1-hb and 2-hb items that most Paladins can't even use.  You will be glad you developed these skills now.<br><br>As for a shield, I agree with earlier posts. The shiny brass shield is a nice shield, magic and relatively easy to obtain.  In and around Crushbone the shield sells for only about 10pp.  It will serve you well for many levels to come. I recommend it.  Don't worry about your bash damage too much. It is never that great.  The main reason to keep your bash skill up is to interupt casters. As you gain levels this will become more and more important. It's not the damage, but the interuption and the stun!<br><br>For example: In Mistmoore, I rarely fear 2 or even three "fighter-type" mobs.  They do some damage but are easily subdued.  However, throw a Caster into the mix somewhere and it suddenly becomes a life-threatening event.  A low-level caster that I could easily dispatch, can take half of my points at level 34 if I'm unable to get to him/her and interupt casting.  Likewise, a mob that is almost dead can go to 3/4ths health with one heal spell if not interupted.  This can also jeapordize the whole battle.  So it's not the damage so much, although it's nice, it's the interuption and stunning, which reduces attacks/damage.  And it is just AWESOME to time your bash, interupt the caster, and then watch them fall without so much as even getting a spell off.<br><br>Once you get higher in levels, you can go with a multitude of shields depending on how you want to play your character.  The Cracked Darkwood Shield is a great shield if you want more strength.  The Crested Mistmoore Shield is great for adding to saves which can be critical when that caster does get a spell off.  The Bark Shield has a nice AC and a nice Agility buff.  There are lots of opportunities.<br><br>Goodluck in CB! I played there for over 10 levels. It is a great zone in your teens!<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>34th Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
