	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>At your level and your location, you can very easily upgrade your shield to a better one.&nbsp;&nbsp;In Crushbone, go to the trainer's hill and kill the Orc Trainer.  On him, there is a Shiny Brass Shield (12AC, +10svmagic....forgot the rest of the stats, but it is a lightsource).  I think it is a fairly rare drop so you may have to kill him a few times before you actually get one. (I lucked out and got mine on teh first kill, as a result of killing him after a train to the entrance).  After about lvl 21, you can obtain the Cracked Darkwood Shield on Highpass Hold off of a named Gnoll (again I forgot to name).  I'm not sure how bash is determined, although logically it would be determined by the amount of AC the shield has.   <br><br> A 2HS weapon that would be nice to pick up is an Axe of the Iron Back (16dmg, 38dly)- true the damage isn't that wonderful but the delay allows you to learn that skill quickly.  Something I really suggest learning at an earlier lvl,  as at lvl 40 I am just now learning to use a 1HB weapon and grow very frustrtated with teh amount of time I have to put in using that type of weapon before I advance on skill lvl.<br><br>As far as the Ghoulbane goes, it is one of the best 1HS weapons in the game at the level in which you can get it.  And, it is essential if you plan on completing the Epic Quests later on in the game for your Fiery Avenger (and later Fiery Defender)- btw these are both 2HS swords.<br><br>Dadin Holyshroud<br>40th season and loyal follower of Brell Selleris<br>&lt;The House Saban&gt;<br>Xev Server<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
