	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ideally, you want to keep all your weapon skills maxxed out. You will want 1HS for when you<br>acquire a Ghoulbane, and 2HS for when you start thinking about the quest swords. For your level, a shiny brass shield is fine. It's magic, which would allow you to bash willowisps and any other MOBs that can only be hit by magic weapons. It also gives light like a GLS, which is nice<br>if you have bad night vision (it frees up a slot that you've had to carry a lightsource in). Bash will never do as much damage as your weapons. Later on when your skill is better, one of the<br>primary things you will use bash for is to stun opponents (disrupting spellcasting, stopping them from fleeing, etc.). I am a level 40 paladin, and I use 1HS/shield as well as 2HS.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
