	   <tr><td colspan=2>Every since the people at VI have fixed it to where Yaulp doesn't reset the timer on the weapon, I have been using Yaulp, most recently YaulpII, every time I got into combat.&nbsp;&nbsp;I'm not really sure if the +10str on Yaulp is really worth it but the added AC is definatly nice.  The mana cost in minimal around 5 for yaulp and 15 for yaulp 2, and it is a relatively quick spell to get off in the heat of combat.  I know that most Pali's whom I group with use it as well, and it does have it's advantages later on.  I'd rather be hit for 58 than 65 when fighting a monster, and killing the moster with half my health meter gone, than have 1 bubble remaining and praying the moster flees before I get knocked around any more.  (an bit of an extreme example, but I was soloing a Giant in Frontier Mountain and both happened to me at lvl 37.)<br><br>Dadin Holyshroud<br>40 season and loyal follower of Brell Selleris<br>&lt;The House Saban&gt;<br>Xev Server<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
