	   <tr><td colspan=2>This idea implies that the Druid will earn money for the Paladin, give him items, let him sell items the Druid gathers, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>While I have nothing against Druids making a living this way, charging for TPs and buffs and other abilities, I would think creating a Druid just to help your Paladin get cash is missing the whole point of the game, and of the Paladin as a class, for that matter. The game is not about money money money and who has the best toys.  While you can't get away from the fact that items are important and play a significant part of the game as a whole, it's not 'JUST' about items and money.  There is much more to be gained from the game than items and cash.<br><br>JMHO<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>34th Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
