	   <a name=98323339841873></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98323339841873><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=98323339841873>LOIO</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=98323339841873#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2438><span id=Scholar>CaledoniaLightbringer</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>100 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Feb 26th 7:23 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>My advice would be to go to Lake of Ill Omen. Most people (that I know about) usually hunt in Oasis till about your level, then move on to LOIO. Personally, I did hunt in oasis till 18, but I found everything there to be very boring.<br><br>How to get to LOIO:<br><br>First things first. You need to get on the right boat. DO NOT take the boat to Kunark that is located in Oasis, because that leads to an evil outpost and you will be KOS. You have to get on the BB boat in FP, which will take you to BB. From there, hop on the shuttles. This will take you to the main boat, and from there to FV, the GOOD outpost. Be sure to get a bind at the bank.<br><br>Secondly, at your level (and at most levels) FV is a VERY dangerous place. I have died many times on the run from FV to LOIO, eventhough it is a fairly short run. The drachnids there are what is dangerous and they are KOS to you, but if you dont get too close, they are usually not a problem. The way you get to Fv is by following the river. From the bridge in FV, go left and follow the lake until you see the statue, and then follow the river. Follow the river right up the hill and everything and you will zone into FV. <br><br>Another thing, FV is very laggy. What tends to happen is that you will be running, only to lag and find a drachnid right infront of you. Just keep running as fast as you can, and try to avoid other ones. Drachnids can see invisible, so that will not help.<br><br>Once you get to LOIO, get ready for the hunting of your life. From the zone, keep following the river until you get to the Lake, and then keep going until south (i think) until you hit the WM. At your level, this is where you will be doing most of your hunting. Watch out on the way for Goblins, and DO NOT go in the water, because the goblins that swim around there are very nasty.<br><br>At the WM, get in a good group and watch the XP roll in. The loot is pretty good to. At later levels, like 24, you can move on to the Sarnaks in the fort, and get even more wicked loot and xp.<br><br>In my opinion, LOIO is the best place to go. Hehe I have tried many other places and none as good as LOIO.<br><br>Hope this helps.<br>&nbsp;<br>Caledonia Delacroix<br>47th Level Paladin<br>Proud Member of <b>The White Cross</b><br>E`ci Server</td></tr>
